    • Constructor Detail

      • MainComponent

        public MainComponent​(ComponentType componentType,
                     int weightage)
        The constructor for an assessment component that has subcomponents. This constructor is used when a main assessment component (e.g. coursework) that has subcomponents. In such case, the component will not have a raw mark of iteself
        Parameters:
        componentType - Name of the main component. Expect an enum type of ComponentType.
        weightage - Weight of the component as of its parent component.

      • MainComponent

        public MainComponent​(ComponentType componentType,
                     int weightage,
                     int rawMark)
        The constructor for an assessment component that does not have subcomponents. This constructor is used when a main assessment component (e.g. examination) that does not have subcomponents. In such case, the component will have a raw mark of itself.
        Parameters:
        componentType - Name of the main component. Expect an enum type of ComponentType.
        weightage - Weight of the component as of its partent component.
        rawMark - The raw mark of the assessment component.

      • getRawMark

        public double getRawMark()
        Ternary operation in this method to get the component's raw marks. If the main component has subcomponents, calls getMark() and get the sum of all subcomponents marks instead.
        Specified by:
        getRawMark in interface Examinable
        Returns:
        raw mark if it dosen't have subcomponents and sum of subcomponent marks if it has subcomponents.

      • getMark

        public double getMark()
        Method to return marks depending on whether main component has subcomponent or not.
        Specified by:
        getMark in interface Examinable
        Returns:
        marks if the main componnet doesn't have subcomponents, otherwise loops through each subcomponent objects using an enhanced for loop and add the marks accordingly to get the overall marks.
